From 18ec1cda9c5f10a8b264d6f17400dd7c4ce565b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Philippe Gerum <philippe.gerum@exail.com>
Date: Wed, 7 Aug 2024 11:47:26 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 152/174] net: dovetail: don't forward stolen skb heads to the
 core

Stolen skb heads are specific to the GRO process, oob buffers are
never part of it. So no need to pass those heads to recycle_oob_skb().

Signed-off-by: Philippe Gerum <philippe.gerum@exail.com>
---
 net/core/skbuff.c | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/core/skbuff.c b/net/core/skbuff.c
index 49b7aa1693db..cbecf89357f6 100644
--- a/net/core/skbuff.c
+++ b/net/core/skbuff.c
@@ -1450,9 +1450,6 @@ void __napi_kfree_skb(struct sk_buff *skb, enum skb_drop_reason reason)
 
 void napi_skb_free_stolen_head(struct sk_buff *skb)
 {
-	if (recycle_oob_skb(skb))
-		return;
-
 	if (unlikely(skb->slow_gro)) {
 		nf_reset_ct(skb);
 		skb_dst_drop(skb);
-- 
2.43.0

